General Martin Dempsey, Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, apologized to Debbie Lee, whose son Marc was killed in Ramadi in August 2006 .
Dempsey wrote a letter saying he regretted that he 'added to the grief' of his son's slain son, who was the first Navy SEAL to die in Iraq .
The 28-year-old was awarded the Purple Heart and Purple Heart for his bravery .